---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "About Us";
const description = "Learn about the mission and calculation standards behind HomeProjectHub. We build transparent planning calculators for homeowners and DIY builders.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical="https://homeprojecthub.com/about/">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6 py-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-[var(--fg-muted)] mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-[var(--fg)] transition-colors">Home</a>
      <svg class="w-3 h-3" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
      <span class="text-[var(--fg-secondary)] font-medium">About</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="pb-6 mb-2 border-b border-[var(--border)]">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-balance mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        About HomeProjectHub
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-pretty">
        Helping US homeowners and DIYers plan projects with transparent formulas, clear assumptions, and practical estimating workflows.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-pretty">
      <p>
        HomeProjectHub was built to make common home improvement estimates easier to check before you shop or call a contractor. When planning a renovation, backyard project, or small residential pour, a clear material estimate can help you budget, compare options, and avoid obvious ordering mistakes.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Our Approach
      </h2>
      <p>
        Every calculator on HomeProjectHub uses visible formulas and plain-language assumptions. We do not use black-box algorithms. Calculator pages show the math, common inputs, and limitations so you can verify whether the estimate fits your project.
      </p>
      <p>
        Material constants such as concrete bag yields, paint coverage rates, and roofing bundle coverage are based on commonly published manufacturer ranges. Always compare the estimate against the label, product data sheet, or contractor quote for the exact material you buy.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Technical Standards
      </h2>
      <p>
        HomeProjectHub is built with modern static web technology (Astro, React, Tailwind CSS v4) to ensure fast load times, zero tracking cookies by default, and strong Core Web Vitals. Your project data is stored entirely locally in your browser.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Contact
      </h2>
      <p>
        Have questions about a calculation, found an error, or want to suggest a new tool? Contact us at <a href="mailto:support@homeprojecthub.com" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:no-underline">support@homeprojecthub.com</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--bg-subtle)] p-5 mt-2">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Methodology & References</h3>
        <p class="text-xs leading-relaxed">
          HomeProjectHub focuses on estimating, not structural design. Volume and area calculators use standard geometry; package counts use stated coverage/yield assumptions; cost references are treated as broad US planning ranges when shown. If a project affects structure, drainage, permits, load paths, electrical, plumbing, or safety, verify the plan with a qualified local professional.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
